The Katsina State police command has arrested a 22-year-old housewife, Fatima Bishir, of Sabon Laying Quarters in Mashi local government area of the state, who faked the kidnapped of her five-year-old daughter in order to implicate her husband’s fiancée, Aisha Musa. The police public relations officer, Gambo Isah, disclosed this while parading the housewife at the command’s headquarter, yesterday, in Katsina, said Fatima Bishir had confessed to the crime. According to him, “On 5/07/2020, at about 0800hrs, she falsely reported at Mashi Division that her little daughter one Fatima Bishir, ‘F’, aged five years old, was missing and strongly suspected the ex-wife of her husband one Aisha Musa, ‘F’, aged 22-years-old of Mashi LGA, Katsina State, whom he wants to return as a wife. She also told us that the Aisha had once lost a daughter to death, and had threatened to revenge her death. “That she mischievously planted the clothes of her alleged missing daughter, Fatima Bishir, in the house of Aisha Musa, where the police recovered red pants and a canvas shoe belonging to the missing child, to implicate her. “She confessed to being the originator of a framed text message sent to her husband Bishir Isyaku, ‘M’, aged 40 years old, threatening him to pay the a sum of N2 million or risk his daughter being killed by the kidnappers.” The PPRO further added that apart from telling us that she took her daughter away herself, Fatima Bishir, also confessed to being the originator of other threat messages sent to the elder brother of the said Aisha, one Sani Musa, aged 28 years old and her ex-husband one Auwalu Haliliu, alias “Al-Jazira” aged 40 years old, both of the same address, implicating them to be among the kidnappers of her daughter.  